About
Dubai Festival City Mall is a shopping mall in Dubai Festival City, on Dubai Creek in Dubai, United Arab Emirates (UAE). Originally opened in 2007, but expanded in 2017.​ Overlooking the serene waters of the creek and iconic Dubai Skyline, Festival City Mall holds a special place in the heart of North Dubai.​ Accessible to shoppers via multiple roadways, public transport and special water taxi stops on the iconic Dubai Creek.​ The mall Festival Bay a great outdoor and used for daily nighttime "IMAGINE Show" Laser, Lights and Fountain show. There is an Abra boat service across Dubai Creek between the Dubai Festival City Mall and the Al Jaddaf Marine Station, close to the Dubai Creek metro station on the green Line of the Dubai Metro. This is operated by the Dubai Roads and Transport Authority (RTA). With over 400 stores and more than 100 Restaurants and Cafes, Food Court with 1000 Seat the largest in Dubai.
Duration: More than 3 hours

1 contribution
Misinformation and broken promises
Jan 2024 • Family
Disappointed about the lack of reliable information on the Imagine show timings.
The website and signage says there should be shows every 30 mins from 7pm on Fridays.
There's a children's carnival with games event and therefore the shows have been suspended.
We asked at the mall information desk and the lady there told us about this but assured us there would be shows at 20:30 and 21:00. She advised to wait till the 21:00 one as it would be the "main" show.
There was a 5 min show at 20:20 and nothing further.
If you're running special events that override your usual programing have the decency to advertise them.
I suggested as much to the lady in the information desk. Her answer was, "no they don't do that on the website".
We came to Festival City specifically to see the Imagine show.
Written January 12, 2024
